Moody's Investor Service Inc said itupgraded Grolier Inc's nearly 116 mln dlrs of debt.    Raised were the company's senior debentures raised to Ba-3from B-3 and convertible subordinated debentures to B-2 fromB-3.    The rating agency cited an improvement in profitabiliy ofGrolier's primary publishing businesses. Moody's said thecompany has lowered its financial leverage as well as itsdependence on the retail sale of encyclopedias.    Grolier has also reduced its exposure to developingcountries, Moody's noted. Reuter&#3;